  <title translate="true">Tip #70</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Heading3"><text styleclass="Heading3" translate="true">Tip of the Day</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="cell-padding:0px; cell-spacing:0px; border-width:0px; cell-border-width:0px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:58px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="TipOfTheDayBulb.jpg" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:328px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">You can use the graphical </text><text styleclass="Class Name" translate="true">MoenTreeView</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> (as demonstrated in the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Class Diagram</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:normal;" translate="true">tool</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">) in your own applications as a plug-in replacement for the normal </text><text styleclass="Class Name" translate="true">TreeView</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. </text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">A point to note, however, is that the moen tree view must be embedded in a </text><text styleclass="Class Name" translate="true">ScrollingDecorator</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> in order to be able to scroll over a large tree.</text><snippet src="Tip_Of_The_Day_Footer"/></para>
  </body>
